By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Monterey Pop (TMC Sunday at 9:05 a.m.), first and still one of the best of the 
rock concert films, features performances by Janis Joplin and Jimi Hendrix. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday Night Fever (KCOP Sunday at 2 p.m.), the 1977 hit starring John 
Travolta as a Brooklyn disco king, has become a cult film in the '90s. 
</P>
<P>
 Black Orpheus (Bravo Monday at 8 p.m., Tuesday at 1 a.m.) is Marcel Camus's 
lush 1959 classic setting the Greek legend of Orpheus in Rio during Carnival. 
