<P>
 LONG QUIET HIGHWAY by Natalie Goldberg (Bantam New Age: $10.95; 238 pp.) . The 
author of "Writing Down the Bones" traces her study of Zen Buddhism and its 
relation to writing as practice. Goldberg avoids the touchy-feely cliches that 
usually creep into American accounts of Zen training and emphasizes the need 
for self-discipline. Her pleasantly low-key journal reminds the reader that 
there is no single path to self-discovery. 
