<TEXT>
<P>
 TATTOO: The Exotic Art of Skin Decoration by Michelle Delio (St. Martin's 
Press: $14.95; 79 pp., paperback original). As Delio is the editor of Skin Art 
Magazine, it's no surprise that this breezy account of the current fad for 
tattoos has a gung-ho tone. Explanations of the various types of tattoos (e. g. 
the ones that look like barbed wire are tribal work ) are supplemented with 
photographs of people adorned with rattlesnakes, flowers, dragons and the names 
of rock bands. The text doesn't mention that an icon of pop culture may quickly 
lose its desirability: If a previous generation had gone in for similar marks, 
would they still want The Bee-Gees and Devo on their arms? 
</P>
