<P>
 MASSENET: "Don Quichotte." Jose van Dam, Teresa Berganza, Alain Fondary, 
others; Toulouse Orchestra and Chorus, Michel Plasson, conductor. EMI CDCB 7 
54767 2.The faded charms of late Massenet are revived here by the masterly 
accomplishment of Van Dam, who brings to the French Don Quixote his usual suave 
virtuosity, as tasteful as it is musical. Fortunately the voice, at the age of 
53, is still there to do his bidding. Much the same can be said for the 
voluptuous contribution of a closely miked Berganza, albeit a little 
thick-voiced these days. Fondary is a self-effacing Sancho. He and Van Dam 
avoid bathos in the death scene, which contains the best music in the score. 
Plasson conducts with appropriate passion. WALTER PRICE 
</P>
