<TEXT>
<P>
 "REVERIE." Carol Rosenberger, piano. Delos DE 3113. This is the sequel to 
Rosenberger's 1989 recording titled "Perchance to Dream."The pianist has 
assembled a program of miniatures and excerpts from larger works that span two 
centuries, but which are united through their introspective natures. Some of 
the performances emerge simple and touching, such as those of Liszt's "Sancta 
Dorothea" and Schumann's "Traumerei." Others, particularly a mannered Arabesque 
No. 1, by Debussy, and a wholly legato Sarabande from J.S. Bach's French Suite 
in G, fare less well. The overall result is monochromatic; it is hard not to 
daydream while listening to this "Reverie," which can only help perpetuate the 
unfortunate and all-too-common concept of music as background. SUSAN BLISS 
</P>
