<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: THE AWARDS PAY OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TV strikes again. As expected, performances on the American Music Awards show 
boosted sales of spotlighted artists. Toni Braxton got a lot of exposure, which 
translated into enough sales to push her "Toni Braxton" to the top of both The 
Times' Southern California pop album chart and the national chart. Whitney 
Houston collected the most awards for "The Bodyguard" soundtrack, and the album 
re-entered the chart at No. 6. Enigma, producer Michael Cretu's techno project, 
debuted at No. 2 with its second album, "The Cross of Changes." Looks like 
Enigma's first album may not have been, as many charged, a fluke novelty hit. 
