<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUYERS, REFI'ERS: GET LOAN HELP AT TIMES HOME FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With mortgage rates moving up from their two-decade low, many Southland 
residents are shifting their house-hunting into high gear. And they quickly run 
into myriad questions about home-loan borrowing. 
</P>
<P>
 At The Times' fifth annual Home Buyers and Sellers Fair, buyers and 
refinancers can get answers to their mortgage questions, pre-qualify for a loan 
at lenders' booths, see how their credit stacks up and check the new loans 
available for first-time and move-up buyers. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair will be held from 9:30 a.m. to 5 p.m., Saturday, March 19, at the 
Anaheim Convention Center in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 A special exhibit area for entry-level buyers with modest incomes called 
"Paths to Homeownership" and sponsored by Fannie Mae (the Federal National 
Mortgage Assn.) will offer programs and advice on how to become a homeowner. 
Also on hand will be representatives of the California Housing Finance Agency, 
FHA, VA and municipal housing programs, which will present their mortgage 
programs for first-timers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
