<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * For a lush, green lawn this spring and beyond, it's time to aerate, 
fertilize, use pre-emergent weed control, mow at 1 1/2-2 inches and water 
deeply and thoroughly. 
</P>
<P>
 * Check out the tuberous begonia bulbs at your garden center.There is a 
delightful array of different varieties that resemble other flowers such as the 
daffodil, camellia, rose or carnation when in bloom. 
</P>
<P>
 * February is a good time to have a special gardening project and one of them 
might be to install a tub garden. Any container can be used so long as it's 
water tight and holds four gallons of water. 
</P>
