<P>
 SANTA CRUZ -- Come out of your shell for the Clam Chowder Cook Off, Saturday 
at the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, 400 Beach St. Awards are given for the 
tastiest Manhattan- and New England-style chowders, and for the best booth 
decor. Cooking: 10 a.m.-noon; tasting begins at 1 p.m. Free admission; $5 per 
tasting kit. The Great Chowder Chase, a 4.5-mile running race, follows on 
Sunday. (408) 423-5590 or (408) 429-3477. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN FRANCISCO -- Sparkling specimens are on hand at the Great San Francisco 
Crystal Fair, Saturday to next Sunday in Building A, Ft. Mason Center. The new 
age rock and mineral show is 10 a.m.-6 p.m. Saturday; 10 a.m.-4 p.m. next 
Sunday. Admission, $4; free for kids under 12. (415) 383-7837. 
