<HEADLINE>
<P>
ONE THAT GOT AWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As a former longtime resident of San Diego and a fish taco devotee, I read 
with great interest your article entitled "Scaling Back" (Jan. 16). However, I 
feel compelled to point out that the article neglected to mention what are 
arguably the best fish tacos in San Diego, if not the world.These fish tacos 
can be found at the Brigantine chain of restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
 My favorite Brigantine is the one in Old Town, which also has a great Sunday 
night happy hour, when you can get both a fish taco and an excellent margarita 
for $3.25. Until I moved to Monterey (where I have yet to find a good fish 
taco), the Brigantine Sunday night happy hour was a regular meeting place for 
myself, my friends and our out-of-town visitors. 
</P>
<P>
 JACQUELINE P. McMANUS, Monterey 
</P>
</TEXT>
