good name and fortune by dragging it through the mud. After all, if Patti Davis 
were not the daughter of former President and Mrs. Ronald Reagan, who would buy 
her books and pay to listen to her speak, and what newspaper would devote an 
entire cover page, plus, to the coverage of Davis' seminar? 
</P>
<P>
 Frankly, I am surprised that with Davis' liberal approach toward politics she 
is not adhering to Clinton's policy of "don't ask, don't tell." I have two 
succinct words for Davis: private life -- get one!  
</P>
<P>
 BETH PENDLETON 
</P>
<P>
