<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCA SUBWAY STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * To Universal/MCA officials may we all say, "For shame," for their effort to 
grab for their corporate pocketbook (Feb. 11) monies generated to help 
alleviate the misery, pain and suffering inflicted by our Jan. 17 earthquake! 
Lives have been shattered; homes have been rendered uninhabitable; businesses 
both small and large have been destroyed, leaving thousands without jobs or 
income. And while area residents and businesses are struggling to piece 
together what they can -- to rebuild, to support themselves and their families 
-- we learn that MCA wishes to use federal assistance funds to change the 
location of a subway stop so that it will better line its corporate pockets. 
</P>
<P>
 Were the sum involved here even just a few thousand dollars, the mere idea of 
raiding earthquake relief funds for such self-serving, profit-driven purposes 
would be distasteful; we are not talking, though, of "just" a few thousand 
dollars, but rather of tens of million, of $40 million, $50 million, $60 
million.  
</P>
<P>
 Let us hope that our public officials will respond accordingly and say no to 
this attempted raid by the greedy on funds intended for the needy. 
</P>
<P>
 EMMA SCHAFER 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
