<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; FIRE DESTROYS MOBILE HOME AND KILLS 4 PETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire early Saturday at the Simi Country Mobile Home Park in Simi Valley 
destroyed a woman's mobile home and killed two dogs and two snakes, a Ventura 
County Fire Department spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire started at 1:47 a.m. in the living room of the mobile home and was 
contained in 25 minutes, said spokeswoman Pam Sears. Investigators are still 
trying to determine the cause. 
</P>
<P>
 The two residents escaped unharmed, Capt. Frank Huneck said. 
</P>
<P>
 Damage was estimated at $30,000. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
