ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Field Trip -- The Sea & Sage chapter of the National Audubon 
Society will hold a field trip to Huntington Central Park at 8 a.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 With fresh "lake" areas at the park, bird activity has picked up, chapter 
officials say.Participants should be ready to get their feet wet as the group 
checks shrubs, trees and the lake area for birds. 
</P>
<P>
 The group will meet at the park's Slater Avenue parking lot, east of Golden 
West Street. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the chapter office at (714) 261-7963. Young 
Audubons -- South Coast Audubon, a chapter of the National Audubon Society, 
will hold a program for children ages 5 to 12 at 6 p.m. Wednesday. The topic 
will be what to do if you find an injured bird. 
</P>
<P>
 The program will be held at the Boys and Girls Club, 1304 Calle Valle, San 
Clemente. 
