<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY WORK REROUTES TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Traffic restrictions will be in effect until 2 p.m. today on segments of the 
Golden State, Antelope Valley and Foothill freeways to allow for quake-related 
demolition and repair work, Caltrans officials said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Northbound and southbound traffic on The Old Road detour will be restricted to 
a single lane along the Golden State-Antelope Valley freeway interchange. 
</P>
<P>
 To accommodate bridge demolition work, northbound and southbound traffic on 
the Golden State Freeway truck bypass route will use a portion of the Antelope 
Valley Freeway detour. 
</P>
<P>
 Traffic on the westbound Foothill Freeway connector to the northbound Golden 
State will have to use the Roxford Street exit and take Roxford to the 
northbound Golden State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
