<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; TELETHON FOR QUAKE VICTIMS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Spanish-language television station KSTV will hold a telethon today to benefit 
Ventura County earthquake victims. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, being run in conjunction with the American Red Cross, will be from 
1 to 6 p.m. at KSTV studios, 6020 Nicolle Ave., Ventura. It is the first 
telethon that the 3-year-old station has attempted, said Promotions Director 
Susan Robles. 
</P>
<P>
 "We felt there was a need for us to try to help our community," Robles said. 
She said the station -- which broadcasts in Ventura, Santa Barbara and San Luis 
Obispo counties -- has already received $5,000 in pledges. 
</P>
<P>
 The station is seeking volunteers, both English- and Spanish-speaking, to 
answer phones during the telethon. For information, call 650-8857. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
