<HEADLINE>
<P>
INDUSTRIAL FIRE FORCES EVACUATION IN BURBANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire at an industrial plating company Saturday night forced authorities to 
evacuate a three- to four-block area around Chestnut and Mariposa streets, 
where they feared toxic fumes from the blaze could endanger residents, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 75 firefighters and three hazardous materials teams fought the blaze 
at Alert Plating Co. that was first reported about 6:30 p.m. said Mike Hand of 
Verdugo fire communications. 
</P>
<P>
 Hand said trace amounts of cyanide gas -- about one part per million -- were 
detected in the air, but that such a level is not considered dangerous. 
</P>
<P>
 A level of 10 parts per million or greater is believed to be unsafe, Hand 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 An unknown number of residents was evacuated to a center at Disney Elementary 
School, Hand said. 
</P>
<P>
 The evacuations were precautionary, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire officials are investigating the cause and origin of the blaze. 
</P>
<P>
 No damage estimate was immediately available. 
</P>
</TEXT>
