<P>
'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT, From Times Staff Writers 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kariya, the Mighty Ducks' first draft pick and fourth overall last June, said 
he hadn't been worried about scoring a goal here and so felt no special relief 
after getting his first Olympic goal Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm not a goal scorer, I'm a passer," he said."But I did feel good today. I 
had a long talk with Coach (Tom) Renney today before the game and I felt like I 
was into the game more, that I had legs." 
</P>
<P>
 Said U.S. goalie Garth Snow, Kariya's teammate at the University of Maine: 
