 "We sent one proposal to the family and they reviewed it with their adviser 
and decided not to accept it," Ferreira said. "It's really frustrating. You're 
negotiating with yourself because they can't send us a proposal (in order to 
preserve Kariya's NCAA eligibility). I've got an idea what they want, and we're 
a long way from that. We're not crying poor, but it's not right. We don't think 
he deserves what he's asking for." 
</P>
