<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION GIRLS' BASKETBALL; VAQUEROS GO THE DISTANCE BUT SURVIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos has been to the Southern Section finals three of the last four 
years, but the Vaqueros, seeded third in Division III-A, almost didn't get out 
of the first round Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho took its first lead with 1 minute 30 seconds left in the game and 
scored a 60-57 victory over visiting San Dimas (14-12). 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos will play at Estancia in Wednesday's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Detra Vickers hit a three-pointer with 2:45 left to tie the score at 51, and 
the Vaqueros (20-6) took the lead a little more than a minute later. 
</P>
<P>
 Akilah Rodgers scored 13 of her game-high 28 points in the fourth quarter as 
Rancho Alamitos outscored the Saints, 23-14. Rodgers also had 17 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Vickers was also a defensive standout. San Dimas's Christen King scored 15 
points in the first quarter, but Vickers held her to only six over the final 
three. 
</P>
<P>
 San Dimas finishes 14-12. 
</P>
