<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION GIRLS' SOCCER PLAYOFFS; CAPISTRANO VALLEY OVERPOWERS SANTA 
MARGARITA IN FIRST ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With half its front line sidelined after first-half injuries, Santa Margarita 
was easy prey for Capistrano Valley, which scored two second-half goals and 
defeated the Eagles, 2-0, in a Division I first-round girls' soccer game 
Saturday at Santa Margarita. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley (20-4-3) will face Claremont, which knocked it out of the 
playoffs last year in the first round, in the quarterfinals Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The game began as an evenly matched showdown between the Cougars, ranked fifth 
in the county, and Santa Margarita (16-6-1), ranked seventh and coming off its 
second consecutive Sea View League championship. 
</P>
<P>
 But when freshman left winger Erin McIntyre left the game because of a 
possible concussion and leading scorer Erica Di Vitis went to the sideline 
because of a knee injury, the Eagles were without most of their offensive 
punch. 
</P>
<P>
 "When Di Vitis went down, that really hurt them," Cougar Coach Harry Hutcheson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley took a 1-0 lead five minutes into the second half, when Kim 
Thompson drove a corner kick into the net. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars scored again 10 minutes later on a breakaway goal by freshman 
Renee Peterson, who was brought up from the junior varsity for the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 The defense tightened its grip on the Eagles the rest of the half behind 
senior Lindsay Light and freshman goalkeeper Sheila Teran, who made two 
one-handed saves late in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division I games: 
</P>
<P>
 Claremont 3, Irvine 3 (Claremont advances in penalty kicks, 1-0) -- Shannon 
Filbin, Heather Swanson and Sarah Denson each scored one goal and Missy Brigman 
recorded eight saves for Irvine (13-6-4). Claremont, the second-seeded team in 
the division, will face Capistrano Valley in the second round Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 3, Torrance 0 -- Christine Tyler, Nicole Price and Laura Lamb each 
scored one goal to lead the host Chargers (22-4-3), who will play Mater Dei in 
the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 3, Chino Don Lugo 0 -- Trisha Steiner scored the first goal for the 
Monarchs 17 minutes into the second half off a double assist from Chrissy 
Whalen and Apollonia Reyes. Whalen and Teresa Buechler also scored for Mater 
Dei (18-5-1).  
</P>
<P>
 Marina 2, Dana Hills 1 -- Amy Rubenstein scored with two minutes remaining in 
the game to give top-seeded Marina the first-round victory. Kristen Palmer also 
scored for the Vikings, which will meet the winner of Simi Valley-South 
Torrance at 3 p.m. Thursday. Shelly Storm scored and Sumon Nicole had 17 saves 
for Dana Hills (14-7-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In Division II: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 2, Trabuco Hills 0 -- Krista Boughton scored the first goal off an 
assist from Genelle Geronsin eight minutes into the second half for Canyon 
(15-5-3). Geronsin added a goal five minutes later. The Comanches will play Los 
Alamitos Tuesday. Trabuco Hills finishes 13-7-4. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 2, Estancia 0 -- Nicole Terry had a goal and an assist and Kaylee 
Whitfield scored a goal for second-seeded El Modena (19-5). The Vanguards will 
play Rancho Cucamonga at 3 p.m. Tuesday. Beth Ferryman recorded 13 saves for 
Estancia, which ends the season at 11-7-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 2, Villa Park 1 (OT) -- Tina Brescini scored two times in the first 
10-minute overtime period and Esperanza (15-5-4) held off a late rally by the 
Spartans (13-3-6). The Aztecs face Redlands in the quarterfinals Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 1, Laguna Hills 0 -- Jamie Pietranowicz scored 18 minutes into second 
half off an assist from Heather Darin. Kennedy (17-4-1) will play the winner of 
Long Beach Poly next Thursday. Laguna Hills is 15-6-5. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 2, Lakewood 1 -- Amber Duarte scored both goals in La Habra's first 
round victory. Duarte's first goal came off a penalty kick 29 minutes into the 
first half after she was tripped on a breakaway. Her second goal was a 25-yard 
shot 19 minutes into second half. La Habra (16-5-1) will play Ventura Buena in 
the quarterfinals. Lakewood finishes at 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division III: 
</P>
<P>
 Moreno Valley Valley View 3, Brea-Olinda 1 -- Michelle Rice scored two goals 
and Larissa Gomez one for Moreno Valley Valley View (18-5-1). Erin Wright 
scored once for Brea-Olinda (11-7-3). DAN ARRITT 
</P>
