<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; ORANGE COAST SWIMMERS SWEEP RELAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast's men's and women's swim teams won Saturday in the Santa Monica 
Relays at Santa Monica Community College. 
</P>
<P>
 The women's team won every event to score 140 points, ahead of Golden West's 
68.Sophomores Brandi Kossub and Sharon Clairemont were on four winning teams 
each. 
</P>
<P>
 The men won seven of the nine relays to score 122 points, ahead of 
second-place Long Beach (76). Grant Ferguson and Richard Ruffini each swam on 
four winning teams. 
</P>
<P>
 The men and women also combined to win two mixed events. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Rancho Santiago baseball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 14, Long Beach 11 -- Brandon Hoalton (3-0) extended his 
winning streak to 16 games with the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Kastelic, batting .552, went three for four with two runs and a run 
batted in for Rancho Santiago (8-2). Daryle Ward went two for four with a 
three-run homer in the sixth and four RBIs, and Jason Minici hit a three-run 
homer in the first. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago will meet Cerritos today in the tournament's winners' bracket. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos 4, Fullerton 3 -- Center fielder John Gardikas had three hits, 
including a double, and Bryan Dunagan (1-2) allowed three earned runs in six 
innings for Fullerton (5-4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast sweeps -- The Pirates won two games at College of the Canyons, 
beating Antelope Valley, 2-1, and College of the Canyons, 5-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelsi Armbruster pitched a two-hitter, giving up only one hit that leave the 
infield, against Antelope Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Against College of the Canyons, Tami Dowlin had two hits and three runs batted 
in for the Pirates. 
</P>
