<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; TITAN WOMEN RALLY TO UPSET VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Despite shooting 31.4% from the field in the second half, the Cal State 
Fullerton women's basketball team erased a 10-point halftime deficit and went 
on to upset UC Santa Barbara, 75-71, in a Big West Conference women's 
basketball game at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans trailed, 45-35, at halftime but rallied behind Shayla Bradshaw, who 
scored 20 points to help them improve to 4-18 and 3-11. Santa Barbara is 13-10 
and 10-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Marissa Frial added 15 points and 10 rebounds and Shefonda Colbert 13 points 
for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Big West women's game: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 64, Nevada 63 -- Michelle Kahler made a jump shot with one second 
remaining to give Irvine the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters (3-19, 2-12) led by eight points with five minutes to play, but 
the Wolf Pack scrambled back and took the lead, 63-62, on Amy Branch's jumper 
with 25 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine, which had not scored in more than three minutes, then called a 
timeout and set up Kahler's game-winner. 
</P>
<P>
 Allah-Mi Basheer led the Anteaters with 15 points and 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 In the National Christian College Assn. Regional Semifinals: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Christian 93, San Jose Christian 85 -- Charles Ross scored a game-high 
30 points and was named most valuable player of the National Christian College 
Assn. men's basketball tournament in San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 Chuck Henderson also had 24 points, as Pacific Christian (24-15) now advances 
to the national finals March 3 in Springfield, Mo. 
</P>
<P>
 Brad Erickson led San Jose Christian (21-10) with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 82, California Baptist 76 -- After trailing the first 29 minutes, 
Concordia took the lead and never trailed. Gitte Mejer had 25 points and 14 
rebounds for Concordia (15-11, 5-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Demetria Dixon had 33 points, including three three-pointers, for Cal Baptist 
(6-20, 1-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 55, Southern California College 45 -- Southern California 
College (21-7, 4-4) trailed by two at the half but was outscored, 26-18, the 
rest of the way. Sanja Simidzija led SCC with 16 points and 19 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 California Baptist 89, Concordia 74 -- Eric Dahl scored 37 points, including 
eight three-pointers, to lead Cal Baptist (13-14, 5-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Vujadin Jovic had 19 points and 10 rebounds and Craig Martin scored 16 points, 
including three three-pointers, for Concordia (15-13, 3-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 77, Southern California College 72 -- Southern California 
College (13-15, 2-8) had a nine-point lead at the half but couldn't hold it. 
Todd Anderson led SCC with 20 points. 
</P>
