<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITAN BASEBALL STREAK REACHES 10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Fullerton baseball team won its 10th consecutive game Saturday, 
beating Cal State Northridge, 1-0, in a nonconference game at Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Millan's eighth-inning double drove Jeff Ferguson home for the game's 
only run. 
</P>
<P>
 Chad Rolish pitched 8 2/3 innings, allowing five hits and striking out five 
for the Titans (11-1), who are ranked third by Collegiate Baseball and off to 
their best start ever. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge (4-4), playing on its home field for the first time since the Jan. 
17 earthquake that damaged much of the campus -- including the outfield wall of 
Matador Field -- stranded 10 baserunners. 
</P>
<P>
 Rolish (3-1), a converted reliever who has yet to pitch a complete game, was 
one out from going the distance before hitting Tyler Nelson and Jason Shanahan, 
both on the foot. Right-hander Ted Silva retired catcher Josh Smaler on five 
pitches for his fourth save. 
</P>
<P>
 In Mountain Pacific Sports Federation men's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA 3, UC Irvine 0 -- Jeff Nygaard had nine kills, and Ross Pier had 21 
assists as the Bruins (8-1, 6-0) remained undefeated conference play with a 
15-3, 15-4, 15-11 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Chad Milling finished with eight kills, and Jason Hinchman had 23 assists for 
Irvine (1-8, 0-7). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 4-10, Redlands 3-0 -- Pitchers Bernie Fancuberta and Leslie Gerbin 
improved to 3-1 in the sweep for Chapman (6-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In Game 1, Katie Shankle-Chriss went two for three with one run batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 In Game 2, Kim Tray went two for two, scoring two runs, with two RBIs. Lisa 
Simpson was two for three, with a double, two runs scored and one RBI. Redlands 
is 0-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 5, California Lutheran 4 -- Rebekah Roberson and Shelly Nelson 
defeated Shana Gilbert and Rhonda McKaig, 6-4, 6-7, 6-3, to give Chapman (1-2) 
the victory. 
</P>
