<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Rene Lync; Craig Stanke, IAN, ; Thuan Le 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HOOP IT UP: The Anaheim Arena will be showcased nationally Monday when Long 
Beach State meets Memphis State in the first men's college basketball game at 
the facility. The 9 p.m. game, part of ESPN's "Big Monday" package, will be 
played in Anaheim because the school could not reach a suitable deal with Long 
Beach Arena. . . . "They welcomed us with open arms," says Scott Cathcart, Long 
Beach State assistant athletic director. Seats are still available. 
</P>
<P>
 VETS & VETS: Veterans of the Vietnam war, both American and Vietnamese, will 
celebrate the lunar calendar's Year of the Dog at a luncheon in Buena Park 
today hosted by the local Vietnam Political Detainees Mutual Assn. . . . "This 
is the first time we have been able to invite our American counterparts to our 
celebration," says organizer Thu Dinh Duong. "They were very receptive to the 
idea." About 4,000 Vietnam veterans and family members are expected to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 FIRING HERE: Former New Hampshire Gov. John H. Sununu has known great 
political highs and lows. Once a power as President Bush's chief of staff, his 
love of office perks led to his downfall. Now he's back on top. . . . As the 
conservative commentator on CNN's "Crossfire," he's much in demand as a public 
speaker. But the Fullerton Republican Women Federated gets him Wednesday for 
free: Sununu is a close friend of one of the members. The group's announcement 
calls it "the first time our club has had a world-renowned and powerful 
national figure." 
</P>
<P>
 WHERE WAS DAN? Following tradition, President Clinton's picture hangs in the 
Federal Building at the Santa Ana Civic Center. But guess how it differs from 
George Bush's. Alongside Clinton's portrait hangs a picture of Vice President 
Al Gore. Bush never shared billing that way with his man Dan Quayle. . . . It's 
a Veep first, federal workers there say. But one of them quipped: "Clinton's 
not able to handle the job by himself." 
</P>
</TEXT>
