<TEXT>
<P>
 If the ski jumpers do as well today in competition as they did Saturday in 
practice, spectators can expect records on the big hill. 
</P>
<P>
 Norwegian star Espen Bredesen got things going with an unofficial record leap 
of 447 feet 8 inches (136.5 meters) off the 120-meter jump, then Jens Weissflog 
of Germany topped him, sailing 449-5 (137 meters). 
</P>
<P>
 "On this hill, I can jump 140 meters," Bredesen said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The first fake ticket of the Games -- or at least the first that was 
recognized -- turned up at the cross-country ski stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The ticketholder, a Swede, said he had bought the ticket from someone else, 
believing it to be genuine. 
</P>
