<P>
BIG WEST ROUNDUP; NEW MEXICO STATE HAS ENOUGH TO HANDLE CAL STATE FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 James Dockery scored 19 points and had 11 rebounds for New Mexico State, which 
used a series of second-half defensive stands to hold off Cal State Fullerton 
in an 85-68 victory at Los Cruces, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans (6-17, 4-11) had several second-half runs, but each time they 
challenged, New Mexico State (19-3, 11-2) answered, finally outscoring 
Fullerton, 17-9, in the closing minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Nevada Las Vegas 80, UC Irvine 64 -- Kebu Stewart scored 16 of his 23 points 
in the second half to lead the Rebels at Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart set an arena rebound record of 24, 17 in the second half, in beating 
the Anteaters for the 11th consecutive time. 
</P>
<P>
 The Runnin' Rebels (11-11, 7-7 Big West) trailed by four points with 13:10 to 
play when Stewart took control of the game. He was fouled on a layup and 
converted the three-point play with 9:54 left to put UNLV ahead to stay 51-50. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters (6-16, 3-11) were led by Todd Whitehead's 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
