<HEADLINE>
<P>
WCC ROUNDUP; BROWN SENDS GONZAGA TO LEAGUE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MITCH POLIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Brown scored 24 points Saturday to lead Gonzaga to a 75-71 victory at 
Portland that clinched the West Coast Conference title for the Bulldogs. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Houle, who had 15 first-half points, led Portland with 18.Jerry Allen and 
Ray Ross added 13 apiece for the Pilots. 
</P>
<P>
 Jerry Allen's three-pointer with 1:44 to play in the first half gave Portland 
(12-15, 5-7) its biggest lead, 39-22. The Pilots led, 60-50, midway through the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
 An 11-3 run in the next 3:22 pulled Gonzaga (19-5, 11-1) to within 63-61. 
Brown's layup with 3:40 tied the game, 69-69. 
</P>
<P>
 John Rillie's three-point field goal with 36 seconds left put Gonzaga ahead 
for good, 72-71. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine 76, San Diego 57 -- It was the final home game for Pepperdine 
seniors Dana Jones and Damin Lopez and both went out in a big way. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez scored a season-high 27 points and Jones broke the school's all-time 
record for rebounds as the Waves won before 1,823 at Firestone Fieldhouse in 
Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones' 11 rebounds gave him 975 for his career, three more than former player 
Levy Middlebrooks. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory moved Pepperdine (14-10, 6-6) into no worse than a tie for third 
in the conference with San Diego (14-9, 6-6). MITCH POLIN 
