<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: USC; HIGH SCHOOL LEADERS TO MEET AT UNIVERSITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The University of Southern California will host its first High School 
Leadership Conference on International Affairs for high school students and 
teachers from 8 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday on campus at the Von KleinSmid Center 
for International and Public Affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, "Southern California's Global Agenda," will feature career 
panels, interactive exercises and discussions led by international relations 
experts.  
</P>
<P>
 Discussion topics include trade and development, governments and global 
environmental problems, immigration policies, cultural differences and 
conflict. 
</P>
<P>
 Edwin M. Smith, USC professor of law and international relations, will deliver 
the keynote address, "Ralph Bunche: Out of Los Angeles," on the Nobel laureate 
who grew up in South-Central. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Linda Cole at (213) 740-2139. 
</P>
