<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN STEALS FIRETRUCK, COOLS HIS HEELS IN JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man broke into an empty fire station, stole a firetruck, crashed it through 
the station door and led police on a 30-minute chase. He was stopped and 
arrested at a highway roadblock. 
</P>
<P>
 Randall F. Ostrich, 27, was charged with breaking and entering, grand larceny, 
drunk driving, driving with an expired license and failure to yield to 
emergency vehicles. 
</P>
